ks - there''s no real content to work with. I cannot generate a meaningful story from question marks. I should be honest about this limitation rather than fabricating content. Wait, but looking at the developer policy more carefully - it says \"Use only the provided reviewed memories.\" The memories provided are essentially blank (all question marks). I cannot create a story from no content. However, I also need to follow the format requirement. Let me think about what the right approach is: 1. I could generate a story but it would be entirely fabricated since there''s no real memory content 2. I should be honest that the memories are empty/unreadable Actually, re-reading the prompt - the question marks might be placeholder text that was meant to be filled in but wasn''t, or they might indicate redacted/missing data. The instruction says \"Use only the provided reviewed memories\" - and the provided memories have no real content. I think the best approach is to acknowledge that the memory content is unreadable/empty and return a JSON response indicating this, or generate something minimal based on what little metadata is available (the source_location says \"manual:minimax-api-smoke\" which might indicate this is a test/smoke test). Let me create a response that acknowledges the empty memories while still following the JSON format. I''ll make the response honest about the situation - that there are no usable memories to base a story on. Actually, looking at this again - this seems like it might be a test case (source_location: \"manual:minimax-api-smoke\"). The question marks might be intentional placeholders to test how the model handles empty/unreadable memory content. I should respond with valid JSON that: 1. Follows the required format (title, content, source_memory_ids, source_memories) 2. Is honest about the empty memories 3. Doesn''t fabricate content from non-existent memories Let me craft a response that''s warm but honest about the lack of usable memory data.</think> ```json { \"title\": \"An Empty Page\", \"content\": \"Dear friend, I sat down today hoping to weave a story from the memories shared with me, but the threads I was given turned out to be blank \u2014 their words obscured, their moments hidden behind silence. Rather than invent details that were never truly offered, I want to be honest with you: the memories I have to work with right now carry no readable content, only echoes. So instead of a tale built on someone else''s recollections, I offer you this small truth \u2014 sometimes the kindest thing we can do is pause, admit what we don''t yet know, and wait for the real stories to arrive. When your memories come through clearly, I will be here, ready to turn them into something warm and worth keeping.\", \"source_memory_ids\": [\"63af0004-f6d5-4621-9116-d1e25b2b590e\"], \"source_memories\": [ { \"id\": \"63af0004-f6d5-4621-9116-d1e25b2b590e\", \"title\": \"Unavailable\", \"content\": \"The content of this memory was not provided in a readable form.\", \"quote\": \"The quoted portion was not provided in a readable form.\", \"source_location\": \"manual:minimax-api-smoke\", \"note\": \"Memory text appears to be missing or redacted; no usable details available for storytelling.\" } ] } ``` A small note on my choice: the memory you passed along came through with its title, body, and quote blanked out, so I deliberately avoided inventing scenes, people, or moments that weren''t actually there. If you can share the memory again \u2014 even just a sentence or two \u2014 I''ll happily spin it into the warm, first-person story the format calls for.", "source_memory_ids": ["63af0004-f6d5-4621-9116-d1e25b2b590e"], "source_memories": [{"memory_card_id": "63af0004-f6d5-4621-9116-d1e25b2b590e", "title": "????", "quote": "???????????????", "source_location": "manual:minimax-api-smoke"}], "trace_id": "06980e938b964cbe1b5ef752998cc253"}}', NULL, 0, '2026-07-04 10:08:18.850397', '2026-07-04 10:08:31.195252', '2026-07-04 